children.name: The typographic scale is designed to keep the number of separate styles to the minimum and is harmonious with our spacing scale. The styles defined in the typographic scale are the primary way to communicate visual hierarchy in text. All type allign to a 4pt baseline grid. Type can be placed outside of the 4pt grid when it’s centered within a component, such as a list item. When placed outside of the grid but centered within a component, text can still appear vertically center-aligned.
